    "body": "I think this issue is [this](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/664348c440ccb4dab3d4c420d6aaee7c688c9b0e/pandas/io/formats/format.py#L1125) selector, which should only apply when where are multiple levels to the index (a MultiIndex)\r\n\r\nI'm not sure how to express this in CSS, so if anyone knows more please chime in. I suppose we could maybe do something like (untested)\r\n\r\n```css\r\n# Always vertical align, for MultiIndex...\r\n\r\n.dataframe tbody tr th {\r\n    vertical-align: top;\r\n}\r\n\r\n# but override for single\r\n.dataframe tbody tr th:only-child {\r\n    vertical-align: middle;\r\n}\r\n```"
